<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-03-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="532" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d532">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">President of the French
                                Republic</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-03-12"><hi rend="italic">March 12,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I have learned with sorrow of the terrible calamity which has befallen
                            France, and tender to its Government and the afflicted families the
                            sincere sympathy of the Government and the people of the United
                            States.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore
                            Roosevelt.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>